-- China's Xi says no hard landing for China economy in 2012
-- 
-- Fri Feb 17, 2012 1:09pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/02/17/us-china-xi-economy-idUSTRE81G1HT20120217

 

 LOS ANGELES  (Reuters) - Chinese Vice President Xi Jinping said on Friday the Chinese economy would experience stable growth and avoid a hard landing this year. 
 "2012 will be a crucial year in driving the 12th five-year plan," he said in remarks in Los Angeles. "China's economy will maintain stable growth ... there will be no so-called hard landing." (Reporting By  Edwin Chan ; Writing by  Paul Eckert )